# MongoDB Authentication - Environment Variables
# 
# IMPORTANT: This file contains sensitive credentials
# DO NOT commit this file to Git!
# Add to .gitignore if not already there

# MongoDB Connection with Authentication
# Format: mongodb://[username]:[password]@[host]:[port]/[database]?authSource=[auth_db]

# Application User Connection (for normal operations)
MONGODB_URL=mongodb://omni_app:SecureApp#2025!MongoDB@localhost:27017/omni_platform?authSource=omni_platform

# Admin User Connection (for database management, backups)
MONGODB_ADMIN_URL=mongodb://omni_admin:SecureAdmin#2025!MongoDB@localhost:27017/admin

# Google API Key (if used)
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# ⚠️  SECURITY NOTES:
# 1. Change the default passwords immediately!
# 2. Store these credentials in a password manager
# 3. Use environment-specific passwords (dev/staging/prod)
# 4. Never log or print these connection strings
# 5. Rotate passwords regularly (every 90 days)

# Password Requirements:
# - Minimum 16 characters
# - Mix of uppercase, lowercase, numbers, symbols
# - No dictionary words
# - Unique per environment

# To generate strong passwords:
# PowerShell: -join ((48..57) + (65..90) + (97..122) | Get-Random -Count 20 | ForEach-Object {[char]$_})
